  'The companies and people in this scenario are fictional.

**Quayside Futures** is a social enterprise led by its Chief Executive, **Marcus Hale**. Its purpose is to regenerate a disused stretch of dockside, the old Custom House and its warehouses, into a public arts, makers and events quarter that blends heritage conservation, community livelihoods and sustainable operation. The vision is set and assured by **Dr Femi Okafor**.

Over three earlier Project Increments the team restored the Custom House as a public gallery, added maker workshops and a café, and opened an events lawn along the quay. Each opened on time and built the Quarter''s reputation for heritage-led, low impact regeneration.

**Project Increment 4** introduces the **Makers'' Wing**, a set of bookable studio residencies, together with a public opening programme of workshops and exhibitions. The Increment must be ready for the autumn arts festival, which is a fixed date. The new offering is expected to draw makers and visitors, lift memberships and income, and keep the Quarter''s standing as a model of sustainable regeneration.

**Scope and deliverables**

- Build and fit out the Makers'' Wing studios using salvaged and locally sourced materials and traditional conservation methods.
- Install accessible visitor facilities that meet heritage and safety standards.
- Launch a membership and online studio booking platform.
- Deliver an opening programme of workshops and exhibitions.
- Embed heritage, safety and accessibility compliance throughout.

**Roles and responsibilities**

| Role | Person | Responsibility |
|------|--------|----------------|
| Business Sponsor | Marcus Hale | Owns the project and its Business Case. CEO of Quayside Futures. |
| Business Visionary | Dr Femi Okafor | Sets and assures the vision and strategic direction for the Quarter. |
| Solution Architect | Greta Lindqvist | Conservation architect. Assures the integrity and quality of the overall solution. |
| Project Manager | Tomas Reyes | Manages timeline, resources, stakeholder engagement and cross-team coordination. |
| Product Owner | Aisha Rahman | Visitor and Programme Manager. Product Owner for both Delivery Teams. |
| Business Advisor, Compliance | Nina Coburn | Heritage, safety and accessibility compliance, spanning the whole enterprise. |
| Business Advisor, Marketing | Sam Doyle | Brand and marketing specialist, part-time and off-site. |
| Process Advisor | Bram Vos | Operations Manager for the Quarter, an operational delivery role. |
| Solution Advisor | Yusuf Demir | Conservation-materials specialist. |
| Delivery Teams | Estate Team and Programme Team | Estate Team: building, conservation, utilities, fit-out. Programme Team: events, membership, retail, IT and booking. |
| Developers | | Trades and conservation craftspeople, programme and curatorial staff, marketing and IT staff. |

